Statement of Qualifications

1. Describe your education and experience in transportation policy and planning.

I hold a Ph.D. in Geography from Kent State University and a Master of Arts in Geography from SUNY Binghamton, with academic training in transportation planning, Geographic Information Systems (GIS), spatial analysis, and quantitative modeling. My education provided a strong foundation in applying data-driven analysis to transportation planning and policy development.

As a Sustainability Transportation Analyst with Caltrans’ Director’s Office of Sustainability, I independently develop analytical methodologies and decision-support tools that support implementation of the Caltrans Strategic Management Plan, the Climate Action Plan for Transportation Infrastructure (CAPTI), and statewide sustainability and equity initiatives. My responsibilities focus on translating planning objectives into practical analytical frameworks that support transportation planning and investment decisions.

I currently lead the technical development of a statewide Speed Performance research initiative by developing analytical methodologies to identify excessive speeding and support future speed abatement planning, aligned with the Caltrans Strategic Management Plan. I also led development of the Transportation Equity Index (EQI) Maintenance Use Case by designing the analytical methodology, conducting statewide implementation analyses, and producing technical recommendations that integrate transportation equity into maintenance planning and resource allocation. In addition, I support broader implementation of EQI by developing analytical use cases and implementation guidance for multiple transportation planning applications.

Another major responsibility is development of the Corridor Prioritization Tool. I developed the analytical methodology, authored the technical documentation, and created a standardized decision-support framework aligned with the Caltrans Strategic Management Plan and CAPTI to support multimodal corridor planning and investment prioritization. I also collaborate with the Vehicle Miles Traveled (VMT) Team to conduct before-and-after traffic volume analyses using StreetLight and Replica, supporting evaluation of transportation projects and rural VMT reduction strategies.

These experiences have strengthened my ability to develop analytical methodologies that support statewide transportation planning and data-driven decision-making.

