2. Describe your education and experience with data analysis in the transportation field, including GIS and statistical software.

I have over ten years of experience applying GIS, programming, and quantitative analysis to transportation planning and policy evaluation. I am proficient in ArcGIS Pro, R, Python, SQL, Tableau, StreetLight, and Replica, and routinely integrate transportation, demographic, and spatial datasets to support statewide planning initiatives.

At Caltrans, I independently develop analytical workflows that transform complex datasets into repeatable methodologies and practical planning tools. My work includes developing GIS workflows, automating analyses in R, creating performance metrics, integrating multiple statewide datasets, and preparing maps, dashboards, and technical reports for planners and decision-makers.

For the EQI Maintenance Use Case, I developed a GIS and R workflow integrating maintenance records, Transportation Equity Index data, demographic information, and operational performance measures. For the Speed Performance initiative, I developed statewide analytical methods and performance metrics to identify excessive speeding using traffic performance data. For the Corridor Prioritization Tool, I developed the analytical methodology and implemented the analytical workflow used to evaluate multiple transportation performance indicators.

I also conducted traffic volume analyses using StreetLight and Replica to evaluate historical project performance and support rural VMT reduction initiatives. These projects required integrating multiple transportation datasets, validating analytical results, and communicating findings that support planning and policy decisions.

My technical experience allows me to transform transportation data into decision-support tools that improve planning, investment prioritization, and program implementation across Caltrans.

