3. Describe your experience with effective communication skills (email, Microsoft Teams, WebEx, phone, in person, etc.).

Effective communication is an essential part of my work because nearly every project requires collaboration across multiple Caltrans divisions and technical disciplines.

I regularly communicate with planners, engineers, GIS specialists, managers, and executive staff through email, Microsoft Teams, WebEx, phone calls, in-person meetings, technical reports, presentations, and technical documentation. I routinely discuss analytical methodologies, explain technical concepts, incorporate stakeholder feedback, and communicate findings to both technical and non-technical audiences.

My work on EQI implementation requires close collaboration with the Director’s Office of Equity and Tribal Affairs to develop use cases, implementation strategies, and technical guidance. I also collaborate with the VMT Team to evaluate transportation project performance and work with multiple offices to develop analytical methodologies supporting statewide transportation planning initiatives.

In addition, I authored the technical documentation for the Corridor Prioritization Tool to ensure future users can consistently understand and apply the analytical framework. Through these experiences, I have become a trusted technical resource within the Transportation Analysis Branch, helping colleagues translate complex analytical results into practical planning applications that support collaborative, data-driven decision-making.

